    feat: Implement GIF functionality and improve Firebase config
    
    This commit introduces a new GIF feature and refactors the Firebase service account key handling.
    
    - Added a new API endpoint () to handle GIF messages, separating it from standard file uploads.
    - Modified the message schema to store GIF search queries in a dedicated  field for better data management.
    - Updated the backend to load the Firebase service account key from an environment variable (), ensuring secure deployment on platforms like Render.
    - Cleaned up the front-end logic to send GIFs without a displayable text message.

